ABOUT:
Blast is a fungal disease caused by Magnaporthe oryzae. It affects leaves, nodes, and panicles, causing spindle-shaped lesions that reduce yield significantly.

SYMPTOMS:
Spindle-shaped lesions with brown borders
Ashy gray centers on leaves
Collar rot on leaf junctions
Node and neck rot in severe cases

PREVENTION:
Use resistant rice varieties
Avoid excess nitrogen fertilizer
Maintain proper field spacing for airflow
Apply recommended fungicides like Tricyclazole
